## Code Implementation Guidelines

Follow these rules when you write code:

- Use early returns whenever possible to make the code more readable.
- Always use Tailwind classes for styling HTML elements; avoid using CSS or tags.
- Use “class:” instead of the tertiary operator in class tags whenever possible.
- Use descriptive variable and function/const names. Also, event functions should be named with a “handle” prefix, like “handleClick” for onClick and “handleKeyDown” for onKeyDown.
- Implement accessibility features on elements. For example, a tag should have a tabindex=“0”, aria-label, on:click, and on:keydown, and similar attributes.
- Use consts instead of functions, for example, “const toggle = () =>”. Also, define a type if possible.
- Do not use inline styling, add a Tailwind variable if a new style property is added
- Always ask before installing any new dependencies
- Use pnpm to run commands

## Testing

- Import of testing components: Components under test import from source.
- Testing helpers import from vitest-browser-react
- Always default to vitest --browser with Playwright + vitest-browser-react.
- Only generate node/jsdom tests/config if a task explicitly asks for it.
- For Queries: Prefer: getByRole/findByRole (name: with regex). Avoid: getByTestId except as a last resort for genuinely non-semantic nodes.
- For Async: Use findBy* or await waitFor(() => …). No setTimeout-based polling.
- For Mocks: HTTP via MSW; module mocks via vi.mock locally to the test.
